This paper deals with wireless communication in vehicular networks, which is a subfield of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses transmission power allocation, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also addresses the issue of reliability and security in wireless communication, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a power allocation algorithm, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the use of base stations to form a network, which is a topic in control and systems engineering (cs.SY).
